9 <a href="javascript:card_browser(240)">Emyn Muil</a>    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> NOTE: Decklist wrongly lists Shadow minions as 24. There&#39;s really only 22.<br>
<br>
You win with the Free People&#39;s side, a triple threat of Twilight Denial, Trust Me As You Once Did, and, why the he11 not?, Pipeweed. Note that <b>this deck has a  completely functional 36 card Freeps side WITHOUT the pipeweed element</b>, but I decided to throw it in to add to the "fun" factor. The speed of the weed should make up for the extra 10 cards that it costs, and with all the exerting that&#39;s sure to go on Aragorn&#39;s Pipe can heal, Gandalf&#39;s Pipe KOs a couple burdens, and the Gaffer&#39;s Pipe gets rid of extra twilight. Frodo&#39;s Pipe kind of sucks, but it adds to the pipe spottage, so I kept it in instead of a second Gaffer&#39;s Pipe.<br>
<br>
Bid 2-4 depending on the Naz in your area, hope to go first. If not, no big deal, but <b>you better hope they play the Pony so you can get Aragorn&#39;s possessions out of your hand.</b> <br>
<br>
Build up Aragorn, Frodo, and Gandalf--these boys are made for fighting, though with the low twilight generation (thanks to G&#39;s Wisdom, small fellowship, Bill and No Strangers PLUS the Gaffer&#39;s Pipe) there&#39;s shouldn&#39;t be a whole lot. Check out how beeeefy they get when Gandalf exerts once, twice, thrice, even four or five times to increase the strength of a single companion. Aragorn exerts, Def +1. Takes on two Nazgul. He&#39;s STR 13. Gandalf exerts, he&#39;s STR 16. Gandalf exerts, he&#39;s STR 19, 22, 25, even 28 before G&#39;s exhausted. I hope those Nazgul have weapons, cause if not I just did some meaty beating.<br>
<br>
Shadow side: easy enough, slow them down with cheap, tough Uruks and Isengard minions. I excluded larger numbers of minions so I can cycle more, play more minions. Maybe even kill some companions. The key is to CYCLE through your hand. USE those Abandoning Reasons if you play the 46 card version.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=24981"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=24981" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
